values:
Well right now its 10h15 pm, just finished watching hockey, and i want to go to sleep... no actually i crave for those moments when i am not the sole controler of my mind. Its really a poetic way to say i crave for not thinking. For braindeadness or at least for not remembering what i though about. I am crazy! I have way too much stuff going on and all of that just because whenever i have a free moment to myself i just keep thinking about not so random stuff that i would want to NOT think about. But let's face it; when you say "do not think about me naked" the first thing you'll think about IS me naked. Well i dont actually think about myself naked, but i think that's beyond the point.

So my point is; do we always fill our lives to quiet down the rampage of our brain, or am i in deep need of psychoanalysis?

Anyways, i'm off to bed. My head hurts.

Boys are easy to figure out. Well a whole 89% of them anyways. But sometimes i do wish they were more complicated than they seem because then we could have far fetched hope.  Hope that what we see is a mask, that what we hear is a lie, hope of change... Yes! i said it change! But then to hope for that is to tie ourselves up in a nonsense world. 

Girls are complicated. I admit it! Though sometimes i do see myself as a boy in a girl's body (ooo boobs! juste kidding) i can get caught, as every other girl, in the intricate design of my mind.  I imagine things that will never happen, i say things that i make myself beleive are true, i see things that aren't there just because it would be so much better if they were.  When a girl says a guy is complicated, it is just because he didn't live up to the expectation or because he didn't react as a girl would have: that is, most of the time, with half truths and twisted statements. I know what im talking about... I am a girl after all. 

So when boys say something, they usually mean it. Unless they look down or avoid you, that usually means that "they are not that into you" (don't i love sex in the city!) And there is another thing about boys: they don't change their mind as quickly as we girls do, but when they do change there is no gray area. So be careful what you wish for... I know i got deceived by my own false hope and tricked imagination... as i keep being tricked by it. But then again i am a romatic, i cant beleive hope is dead.

To all girls out there *cheers*

To all boys out there *kiss* - I know you dont really mean it, its your Y chromozone -
